# Implementation guidance

- Use server/clients/prismaClient.ts and redisClient.ts
- Wrap withErrorHandler.ts or handleApiError.ts; normalize Plaid errors via plaidApiError.ts
- Validate inputs with Zod (app/schema/zod.ts) and/or dedicated schema files (e.g., schema/plaid.ts)
- Enforce auth (server/middleware/auth.ts) and use requireAdmin.ts for admin-only routes
- For long-running work (syncs, recalculations), enqueue via server/queues/* or expose tasks/* endpoints with care

# Adding a new endpoint

1) Create app/server/api/<path>.<method>.ts
2) Parse request and validate with Zod
3) Authorize early using session helpers (getUser.ts, accountAccess.ts, accountMembership.ts) and guards
4) Delegate core logic to a service in server/services/*
5) Add unit tests under server/api/__tests__
6) If consumed by the UI, expose a composable (app/composables) or Pinia store action; add Playwright coverage if UX changes
